    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>After an 11-week trial and voluminous testimony about lives of the rich and famous, a jury in Santa Monica, Calif., acquitted Susan H. McDougal of all charges of embezzling $50,000 from the conductor Zubin Mehta and his wife, Nancy.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>After an 11-week trial and voluminous testimony about lives of the rich and famous, a jury in Santa Monica, Calif., acquitted Susan H. McDougal of all charges of embezzling $50,000 from the conductor Zubin Mehta and his wife, Nancy.</p>
        <p>Jurors said prosecutors failed to make a credible case against Ms. McDougal, the Mehtas' former bookkeeper and President Clinton's onetime partner in the Whitewater deal. She  still faces Federal criminal contempt of court charges in Arkansas for her refusal to answer questions from the independent prosecutor Kenneth W. Starr.</p>
        <p>TODD S. PURDUM</p>
      </block>
